    • Method Detail

      • getCompleteShipmentDetails

        org.w3c.dom.Document getCompleteShipmentDetails(YFSEnvironment env,
                                                org.w3c.dom.Document inXML)
                                         throws com.yantra.yfs.japi.YFSException,
                                                java.rmi.RemoteException
        getCompleteShipmentDetails API is intended to be used in the Shipment Tracking task. This was created to reduce the logic in the UI (at the runtime). Performance of the Shipment Tracking task is thus improved. This API gives the complete information that Shipment Tracking task needs.

        ItemTrackingLevel attribute in OrderStatus element or TrackingLevel attribute in the ItemTrackingLevel element. ItemTrackingLevel attribute is present in the OrderStatus element. ItemTrackingLevel is present under the OrderLine element. Under this ItemTrackingLevels element multiple ItemTrackingLevel elements appear, if there are multiple item tracking levels. ItemTrackingLevel element has two attributes TrackingLevel and TrackingLevelDesc.

        ItemTrackingLevel attribute or TrackingLevel attribute in the ItemTrackingLevel element can have the following values
        00: This value indicates that no panel has to be created.
        10: This value indicates that separate panels have to be created for the each Work Order. This value can be present only in the OrderLine element. If this value is found, loop through the WorkOrder element under the OrderLine element and create separate panel for each WorkOrder element.
        20: This value indicates that separate panels have to be created for each Shipment Container. This value is present only in the OrderLine element. If this value is found, loop through the Container element under the OrderLine element and create separate panel for each Container element.
        30: This value indicates that separate panels have to be created for each Shipment Line. This value is present only in the OrderLine element. If this value is found loop through the ShipmentLine element under the OrderLine element and create separate panel for each ShipmentLine element. The ShipmentLine(s) that is already present in the container is removed under the ShipmentLines element.
        40: This value indicates that separate panels have to be created for each Order Status. This value is present in both OrderLine and OrderStatus elements. If this value is found in Status attribute of the ItemTrackingLevel element under the OrderLine element, loop through the OrderStatus elements that have this value in ItemTrackingLevel attribute. Create separate panel for these OrderStatus elements.
        45: This value indicates that separate panel has to be created for Backorder Status. This value is found in OrderLine and OrderStatus elements.
        50: This value indicates that separate panels have to be created for each Assignment. This value is found only in OrderLine element. If this value is found, loop through the Assignment element under PromiseLine element and create separate panel for each Assignment element.
        60: This value indicates that separate panel has to be created for Cancelled Status. This value is found in OrderLine and OrderStatus elements. If this value is found, loop through the OrderStatus elements that have this value and create separate panel for each.
        70: This value indicates that separate panel has to be created for Order Line Holds. This value is found in OrderLine element. If this value is found, loop through the OrderHold elements and create separate panel for each OrderHold element.

        Related Documents
        Input XML Input DTD Output XML Output DTD Error XML Error DTD

        User Exits:

          com.yantra.pca.ycd.japi.ue.YCDGetTrackingNumberURLUE
            This user exit is called to get the url to view the tracking information of the shipment. The error code YCD00028 is thrown if an exception occurs during the invocation of this user exit.

          Events Raised: None

          Audits: None

          Pre-conditions: None

          Post-conditions: None

          Output Template Support: Yes

          Database Extensibility Support: Yes

          Additional Information



        Parameters:
        env - Required. Environment handle returned by the createEnvironment API.
        inXML - Required. Contains attributes of the address that is to be verified. For more information, see the associated input xml files.

        Returns:
        An XML document that contains the address details as well as a status representing if the verification succeeded, failed, or could not be performed. For details on the output, refer to the associated output files.
        Throws:
        java.rmi.RemoteException - Java's default remote exception handler.
        com.yantra.yfs.japi.YFSException - Exception containing error codes in the standard error files.
